comment_data.body:
@DavidGamba ASCIIdoc seems interesting, but it has some minor problems: it is less popular then ReST (documentation for most of Python projects is written in ReST, which means there are lots of developers familiar with it, ASCIIdoc is neither language-bound or positioned as a main documentation format for any mainstream languages), it has unfamiliar syntax (though still better then ReST), I know no site like ReadTheDocs for ASCIIdoc and I know no doxygen bindings.

Since `equery depends asciidoc` shows that Git, XCB, various other X11 thingies, ninja and awesome do use it it is not unlikely that there is a documentation hosting for this or doxygen integration. Can you say something about this?

Note that I would not say that any of the mentioned issues are stoppers. They just make ReST look slightly better, even though I am not fond of its syntax.
